# Corporate route list consumed by both OpenVPN (split-tunnel) and Xray routing.
# One `route <network> <netmask>` per line. Blank lines and `#` comments are ignored.
#
# Rule of thumb: list every subnet or host that must exit via the corporate tunnel.
# Anything not listed here will NOT be pulled into tun0 and will go out via the
# default outbound (see routing config).

# Ignore anything the server pushes (routes, DNS, gateway) - we use the list below instead.
route-nopull

# VPN subnet itself (adjust to match your OpenVPN server's tunnel network)
route 10.8.0.0 255.255.255.0

# Corporate private subnets (replace with your own)
# route 10.0.0.0   255.255.0.0
# route 10.1.0.0   255.255.0.0

# Specific public hosts that live behind the corporate perimeter
# route 203.0.113.10   255.255.255.255
# route 203.0.113.11   255.255.255.255
